In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims October 2009 as National Disability Employment Awareness Month. He emphasizes that fair access to employment is a fundamental right for all Americans, including the 54 million people living with disabilities in the country. The President recognizes that a job can provide financial stability, maximize potential, and help individuals achieve their dreams. While progress has been made in providing equal employment opportunities, there is still much work to be done. The President calls for effective policies and practices that increase employment opportunities for individuals with disabilities. He highlights the importance of providing support and services to ensure their success in the workforce. The President also mentions the need to strengthen and expand educational opportunities for individuals with disabilities. He acknowledges the contributions made by individuals with disabilities in shaping the identity of the nation and calls for an inclusive work culture that welcomes the skills and talents of all qualified employees.